5	 *   AC-1: Malformed line → parse_error emitted, parser continues.
6	 *   AC-2: stream.text events carry blockId + textDelta; final:true on content_block_stop.
7	 *   AC-3: stream.usage carries all four token fields.
8	 *   AC-4: rate_limit_detected raised when rate_limit_event status !== "allowed"; reset_at extracted.
9	 *   AC-5: Tested against empirically captured fixture files (not synthetic payloads).
10	 *   AC-6: stream.tool_result always follows matching stream.tool_use within a session.
11	 *
12	 * Review criteria coverage:
13	 *   RC-1: feedChunk() splits on \n only; tested with 1-byte chunk size.
14	 *   RC-2: Rate-limit detection pattern matches the empirically verified format from docs/research/.
15	 *   RC-3: parse_error events are emitted (SQLite persistence is Pipeline Engine's responsibility).
16	 *   RC-4: No streaming parser library — StreamJsonParser is an EventEmitter with feed/feedChunk.
17	 *
